  "text": "]), is actually base-point free. They suspect so, but don't give a complete proof. In this section we prove that |D 0 | has at most four base points (see Theorem 3.8). This result was inspired by the paper [CITATION_1] , which contains a careful analysis of the surfaces belonging to the linear systems | − K E(3) | and | − K E(3) + η i |. Let us denote by X ηi the unique element of | − K E(3) + η i |, and let A ∈ | − K E(3) |.",
